        <body>
            <div type="poem">
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="aabb" n="1"><head>I</head>
                    <l><hi rend="smallcaps">Ye</hi> have darkened mine honour, and branded my name;</l>
                    <l>Ye have quenched its remembrance in silence and shame;</l>
                    <l>Yet the heart ye called craven, unbroken, hath borne</l>
                    <l>The voice of your anger,&mdash;the glance of your scorn.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="aabb" n="2"><head>II</head>
                    <l>But the life that hath lingered is now in mine hand;<ptr target="targetneeded"/></l>
                    <l>My waiting was but for a lot of the land,</l>
                    <l>Which His measure, who ruleth the battle array,</l>
                    <l>May mete for your best and your bravest to-day.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="aabb" n="3"><head>III</head>
                    <l>My kinsmen,&mdash;my brothers,&mdash;your phalanx is fair;</l>
                    <l>There's a shield, as I think, that should surely be there;</l>
                    <l>Ye have darkened its disk, and its hour hath drawn near,</l>
                    <l>To be reared as a trophy, or borne as a bier.</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
